<item>
            <title>[SPARK-21588] SQLContext.getConf(key, null) should return null, but it throws NPE</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-21588</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SQLContext.get(key) for a key that is not defined in the conf, and doesn&apos;t have a default value defined, throws a NoSuchElementException. In order to avoid that, I used a null as the default value, which threw a NPE instead. If it is null, it shouldn&apos;t try to parse the default value in `getConfString`&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13091436">SPARK-21588</key>
